 <title>Unitized body</title>
 <definition>
  <definitionText>The term unibody or unit body is short for unitized body, or alternatively unitary
      construction design. This engineering approach of a vehicle describes "of a vehicle, a
      one-piece frame and body structure" A "type of body/frame construction in which the body of
      the vehicle, its floor plan and chassis form a single structure.</definitionText>
  <definitionSource>
